.TH "rio_mport_get_feature" 9 "rio_mport_get_feature" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rio_mport_get_feature \- query for devices' extended features
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "u32" rio_mport_get_feature
.BI "(struct rio_mport * port "  ","
.BI "int local "  ","
.BI "u16 destid "  ","
.BI "u8 hopcount "  ","
.BI "int ftr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "port" 12
Master port to issue transaction
.IP "local" 12
Indicate a local master port or remote device access
.IP "destid" 12
Destination ID of the device
.IP "hopcount" 12
Number of switch hops to the device
.IP "ftr" 12
Extended feature code
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Tell if a device supports a given RapidIO capability.
Returns the offset of the requested extended feature
block within the device's RIO configuration space or
0 in case the device does not support it.
